@kelea99 Looking for PO input for prioritization here. This issue essentially means that the feature to detach and attach resources from parent resources (originally requested by the Cicognara project) does not work. We were wondering if you have received any questions about it, or if folks just aren't really trying to use that feature right now. It has been affecting @tventimi occasionally, but so far we've been able to handle these problems as they've come up. Do you think we should look to prioritize this issue soon? If yes, @kelynch suggested that maybe we could put it in the work cycle starting september 7th, which will have a focus on virtual reading room requirements. Thanks!

@hackmastera I know this is the manual way @roelmoon showed me how to add resources to parent resources, if/when needed. Since batch ingest now works, and until we hear more use cases, I would normally suggest holding off on prioritizing this issue. My only hesitation is the the CDL workflow and continuous incoming requests. if/when we have need to start adding resources to parents (if more volumes are requested for CDL), I can see this potentially becoming a bigger issue than it is now. thoughts?

@kelea99 we haven't seen any multivolume CDL items yet, or parts of multivolume items. We did ask Peter to give us the items numbers if any come in because we'd like to test that. So I'd say let's not act based on that use case until we have it in hand.

@hackmastera do you have a ETA for the items numbers Peter? Or is there a way to view the pending/fulfilled requests that have/are coming in for them? If not, my two cents is proceed as you have been on a case by case basis (which sounds few and far between) until we get more use cases. However, we should probably start logging the number of requests for this.
